Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.75,0:00:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.02,0:00:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some highlights\Nfrom this month’s program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.86,0:00:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do if we encounter spiritism
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in some form?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.50,0:00:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can we help
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,others break free from it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.67,0:00:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This dramatization will provide\Nsome valuable principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.94,0:00:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve all beheld the wonders of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.71,0:00:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s beautiful music video
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will move us to pause,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.61,0:00:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,think, and thank Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.78,0:00:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for his magnificent works.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.29,0:00:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And we go to world headquarters\Nto visit another museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.92,0:00:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how, in our time, Jehovah is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.23,0:00:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,blessing “a people for his name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.60,0:00:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the August 2019 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.32,0:01:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our broadcast this month has the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Cherish Your Privilege of Prayer.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.66,0:01:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think it’s appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to label prayer as a miracle?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.67,0:01:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles are described
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.20,0:01:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in our New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.10,0:01:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“Glossary of Bible Terms”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.24,0:01:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as “actions or phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.64,0:01:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“that surpass all powers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.98,0:01:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“known to humans and are attributed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.25,0:01:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to a supernatural agency.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.08,0:01:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Does prayer fit that description?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.82,0:01:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment you say a prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.19,0:01:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your innermost thoughts and feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.39,0:01:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are communicated instantly to the Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from wherever you are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.06,0:01:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—even if you pray silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.23,0:02:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s certainly\Nbeyond any power that humans know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.04,0:02:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the fact that a human
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.87,0:02:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,can call out to God in prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and be heard by him
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.21,0:02:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is truly a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.35,0:02:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s only\Nby the undeserved kindness of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.05,0:02:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can approach\Nhis heavenly throne in prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.96,0:02:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Today our lives are very complicated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.56,0:02:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and, in some cases, very troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.56,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether young or old, there are times
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we may feel overwhelmed with our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.57,0:02:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At other times,\Nwe may simply feel alone and helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.48,0:02:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul says that prayer will help.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.62,0:02:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open your Bible to Philippians 4:6
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.79,0:02:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and listen\Nto his spirit-inspired recommendations:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.63,0:02:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be anxious over anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“but in everything by prayer and supplication
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.33,0:03:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“along with thanksgiving,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.43,0:03:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,let your petitions be made known to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.60,0:03:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So Paul is saying\Nthat in all circumstances of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.77,0:03:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer is essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.18,0:03:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,While no one around us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.58,0:03:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,can see the inner struggles we may be having,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.68,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sees them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What will he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verse 7:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the peace of God\Nthat surpasses all understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“will guard your hearts\Nand your mental powers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.16,0:03:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of Christ Jesus.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.97,0:03:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This incomparable “peace of God”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is an unusual tranquillity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.27,0:03:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoyed by Jehovah’s dedicated servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.41,0:03:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,even in the most trying circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.08,0:03:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you felt that inner peace
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.75,0:03:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that results\Nfrom intimate communication with Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:04:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How much we benefit from prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.72,0:04:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is closely related to the strength
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.43,0:04:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of our personal relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.67,0:04:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A key factor in that relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.07,0:04:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is found at Psalm 37:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Trust in Jehovah and do what is good;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.18,0:04:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,reside in the earth,\Nand act with faithfulness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.81,0:04:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Likely you’d agree that when we need\Nto talk to someone about our worries,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.35,0:04:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we go to a trusted friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.35,0:04:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because we’ve developed\Na relationship with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.43,0:04:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows us and our situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know we can count on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.43,0:04:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,More than ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.50,0:04:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we need\Na close personal relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.24,0:04:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,For that to be possible, we must be convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.61,0:04:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah knows\Nwho we are and that he understands us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.61,0:05:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—our situation, our worries,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.62,0:05:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,our concerns, and our needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what Jehovah promises
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.72,0:05:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in verses 4 and 5:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.43,0:05:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Find exquisite delight in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will grant you\Nthe desires of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.37,0:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“Commit your way to Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.60,0:05:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,rely on him, and he will act in your behalf.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does know who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.48,0:05:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He understands us better than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,even better than we understand ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.15,0:05:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He invites us to trust him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.22,0:05:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and he promises to act in our behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.39,0:05:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The miracle of prayer lets us experience
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s love in a truly intimate way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.27,0:05:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Father personally\Ntakes the time to listen to us;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.00,0:05:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he has not delegated that to anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.14,0:06:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you might be wondering,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.34,0:06:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‛Why would the Creator\Nof the universe want to listen to me?’
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.35,0:06:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspired answer at 1 Peter 5:7 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.35,0:06:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because he cares for you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Your determination to keep doing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.36,0:06:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the best you can to serve him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.69,0:06:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in spite of all the problems you face
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.60,0:06:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,endears you to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.10,0:06:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He feels for you and is eager to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that make you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,At Psalm 116:1, it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.51,0:06:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“I love Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.51,0:06:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“because he hears my voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,my pleas for help.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.25,0:06:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we can’t see him listening to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s as if we feel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s loving arms around us when we pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the more we pray,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.57,0:07:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the more our love and trust in him grows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.30,0:07:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What else will help us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.34,0:07:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to build our love\Nand trust in our God, Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.71,0:07:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s more than recognizing\Nthat he hears our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.35,0:07:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We must be convinced
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.35,0:07:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that he answers our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.65,0:07:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What evidence do we have\Nthat Jehovah answers prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at some\Nspecific answers to prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,both past and present.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.10,0:07:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your Bible to 2 Chronicles chapter 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.37,0:07:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When Judah was threatened\Nby the combined forces
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of Ammon and Moab\Nand the mountainous region of Seir,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.21,0:07:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,King Jehoshaphat\Nhumbly prayed for Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.01,0:07:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 12, he prayed:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.92,0:07:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“O our God,\Nwill you not execute judgment on them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.89,0:07:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“For we are powerless
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“before this large crowd\Nthat is coming against us;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“and we do not know what we should do,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.06,0:08:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but our eyes are toward you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.50,0:08:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What was Jehovah’s answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.77,0:08:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no voice from heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.47,0:08:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah caused a prophet to speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.71,0:08:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 15 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here is what Jehovah says to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.51,0:08:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do not be afraid or be terrified\Nbecause of this large crowd,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.79,0:08:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for the battle is not yours but God’s.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.12,0:08:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then verse 17 continues:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.99,0:08:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will not need to fight this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.83,0:08:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take your position, stand still,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.87,0:08:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the salvation\Nof Jehovah in your behalf.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.80,0:08:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you note the formula?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.81,0:08:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s dedicated servant\Nis facing a serious problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He prays specifically,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he remains attentive to the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.02,0:09:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer may have seemed\Nstrange to Jehoshaphat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah didn’t provide a battle plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As strategies go, just walking out
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet the enemy\Ndoesn’t sound like a very good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehoshaphat discerned
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was the answer from Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.24,0:09:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and he let it direct his actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.27,0:09:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah fought for Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.85,0:09:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,by striking confusion\Ninto the ranks of the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they slaughtered one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoshaphat’s prayer was answered
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.19,0:09:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in a mighty way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.89,0:09:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We have examples in the first century
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.56,0:09:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of collective prayers being answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.76,0:09:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,One occasion was when King Herod
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,was out to gain the favor of the Jews,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.07,0:09:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so he had the apostle Peter imprisoned
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and placed under heavy guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What would the congregation do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:09:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Acts 12:5 gives us the answer:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.12,0:10:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Peter was being kept in the prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.92,0:10:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but the congregation\Nwas intensely praying to God for him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Jehovah answer their prayers\Nin behalf of Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.99,0:10:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The account in verses 7-11 tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that an angel of Jehovah\Nled Peter out of jail
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.94,0:10:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and delivered him to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.11,0:10:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how these events must have drawn
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.41,0:10:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Christians in Jerusalem closer to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.68,0:10:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when they saw\Nthat he had answered their prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.79,0:10:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.65,0:10:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the example\Nof our brothers in South Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the years,\Nmore than 19,000 of our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.16,0:10:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have been imprisoned\Nas conscientious objectors
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to military service.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you personally pray\Nin behalf of these brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:11:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that they might endure in their faith
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.94,0:11:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or that they might be released from prison
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if it was Jehovah’s will?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.35,0:11:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sure that you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.35,0:11:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, many of you prayed\Nfor these brothers by name,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.42,0:11:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,just as the congregation in the first century
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.93,0:11:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,prayed in behalf of Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.29,0:11:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,With what result?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2018, a series\Nof court rulings in South Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.13,0:11:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,finally recognized conscientious objection
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.70,0:11:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to military service for religious reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.24,0:11:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as a fundamental human right,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.48,0:11:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and our brothers\Nwere gradually released
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.18,0:11:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from their prison bonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.19,0:11:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Jehovah hear our prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.72,0:11:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in behalf of these dear brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.36,0:11:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As a worldwide brotherhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there can be no doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.43,0:11:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that our incessant prayers to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:12:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,were a major factor\Nin these marvelous developments,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and we praise and thank Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.97,0:12:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that he’s heard our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.98,0:12:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this review\Nof how Jehovah answered the prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.55,0:12:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of his servants\Nin the past and present do for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.22,0:12:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t it build confidence that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.69,0:12:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is listening to and acting on\Nthe prayers of his people?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.96,0:12:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle John had that confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.86,0:12:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote at 1 John 5:14:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.23,0:12:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this is the confidence\Nthat we have toward him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“that no matter what we ask\Naccording to his will,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.31,0:12:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he hears us.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But now the question is:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.88,0:12:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When was the last time\Nthat Jehovah answered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.88,0:12:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,one of your personal prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.65,0:12:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We spend much time on learning
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.49,0:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how to pray and what to pray for,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.76,0:12:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but do we put forth enough effort
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in identifying the answers to our prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For us to have the closeness to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we must be certain that he’s listening
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.71,0:13:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and responding to our personal prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.38,0:13:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It may not always be readily discernible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.78,0:13:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just how some prayers are answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.05,0:13:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Take time to meditate on Jehovah’s response
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.75,0:13:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to your prayerful requests.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.49,0:13:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re married,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.49,0:13:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,freely discuss matters\Nthat you have prayed for in common
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.30,0:13:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and how Jehovah\Nmay be answering those prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.87,0:13:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Be observant and alert to things\Nthat are happening around you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.71,0:13:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn to connect these things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.78,0:13:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with the answers to your prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Make your prayers more specific,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.52,0:13:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll become\Nmore keenly aware of Jehovah’s answers
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:14:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—even though they may be subtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.72,0:14:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Identifying your answered prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.43,0:14:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,will make Jehovah more real to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.53,0:14:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This process\Nof identifying answers to our prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.40,0:14:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,should be learned early on\Nin one’s spiritual development.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.17,0:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot take it\Nfor granted that our children
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or our Bible students\Nwill connect the answers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.58,0:14:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they receive to the prayers they’ve offered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.75,0:14:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,One Witness said,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.95,0:14:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“I find that people feel closer to God
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.59,0:14:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“if I help them to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.16,0:14:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,answers to their prayers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.00,0:14:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we can’t identify
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.80,0:14:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer to one of our prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.07,0:14:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean\Nit wasn’t according to Jehovah’s will?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.41,0:14:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two important factors\Nthat might be involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.05,0:15:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One is that Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.25,0:15:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the best time and way
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.35,0:15:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to answer our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.72,0:15:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He takes all matters into consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer may not come
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,according to our timetable, but it will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we must be patient
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.24,0:15:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep looking for the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.07,0:15:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The second factor that Jehovah considers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is the issue raised by Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.58,0:15:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding man’s integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen again to the challenge Satan makes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.75,0:15:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded at Job 1:10, 11:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.86,0:15:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Have you not put up a protective hedge
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.06,0:15:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“around him and his house\Nand everything he has?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.56,0:15:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“You have blessed the work of his hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.20,0:15:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his livestock\Nhas spread out in the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.44,0:15:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“But, for a change, stretch out your hand
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.54,0:15:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“and strike everything he has,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will surely\Ncurse you to your very face.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah permitted this issue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.51,0:16:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to be raised out of love\Nfor his intelligent creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.52,0:16:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He permitted Job to undergo a test
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by Satan before the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.83,0:16:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gives his creatures the privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of proving the Devil a liar\Nand of removing the slander
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not only from God’s name
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.14,0:16:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but also from their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.94,0:16:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah, seeing the entire issue,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.94,0:16:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,may allow his servants to endure trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.18,0:16:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn’t mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.55,0:16:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s not answering\Nthe prayer of the afflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.99,0:16:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When we are under trial,\Nwe may have prayed for relief,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.62,0:16:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but we may have also prayed:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.53,0:16:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let your name be sanctified.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.40,0:16:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We must remain convinced that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:17:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will not simply answer a prayer;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,he will provide the best answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.74,0:17:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it true that\Nwhen we maintain our integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.68,0:17:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,even through serious illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.81,0:17:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be a tremendous witness to others?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.15,0:17:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the case with Jerod Septer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Word says:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember, then, your Grand Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the days of your youth,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.26,0:17:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,before the days of distress come.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.04,0:17:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And “the days of distress”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.20,0:17:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,—they arrived early on Jerod at 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.27,0:17:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerod was diagnosed\Nwith lymphoma cancer in the middle of 1991.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.61,0:17:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We started trying\Nto figure out how we could get him
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.88,0:17:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the treatment that he needed,\Nof course, but in no way would we accept
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.35,0:17:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a blood transfusion, and neither would Jerod.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jerod was in the hospital,\NChild Protective Services
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.69,0:18:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,did investigate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.23,0:18:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They were concerned there was negligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just adding to the pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.63,0:18:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it turned out,\Nthey backed completely away from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.84,0:18:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They realized that we hadn’t been negligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.87,0:18:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we faced different situations,\Nwe’d pray at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not to have miraculous answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but for Jehovah to open our eyes\Nand to be able to find things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.52,0:18:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seemed as though\Nhe was really directing us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we could take care\Nof ourselves spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,through this situation as well as take care\Nof Jerod’s medical needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.03,0:18:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.37,0:18:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,many times falling on my knees
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.27,0:18:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and praying and thinking: ‘This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.80,0:18:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m tested beyond what I can bear.’
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah would strengthen me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.38,0:18:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And someone would come,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.01,0:18:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or they would say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.05,0:18:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And they fed us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.95,0:18:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The brother made a schedule, and he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.59,0:18:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’re going to feed these friends.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.02,0:19:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the brother’s instructions were:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“You don’t bring it\Nand just drop off the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay with those friends.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.33,0:19:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me cry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.10,0:19:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—the love and the care that we experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the hallways of this hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.37,0:19:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—1,500 miles (2,400 km) away from our home—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.31,0:19:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,started filling up with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.81,0:19:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, that was answering prayers too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hard for us\Nto get out of the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so they recorded talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They would look us in the eye,\Nand they’d say:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.99,0:19:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now, you need to listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.82,0:19:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It will keep you strong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.92,0:19:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerod was worried about us,\Nand he made it clear
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.09,0:19:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was going to be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He just didn’t know if we were going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.40,0:19:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He died
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.94,0:19:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in June of 1992.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.51,0:19:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He was at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.94,0:19:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last thing he said to us was,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:20:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Work hard so we can all be together again.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.36,0:20:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s numbing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.13,0:20:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s almost like\Nyou’re living a nightmare
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.43,0:20:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because you never think\Nthat those things will happen to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.94,0:20:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.94,0:20:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want people to see me cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.54,0:20:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want pity, and I didn’t—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.15,0:20:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.15,0:20:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—those negative feelings—\Nmy imagination ran wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.52,0:20:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What helped me, I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.32,0:20:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was Gary putting into my heart and mind
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.99,0:20:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.10,0:20:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a challenge for all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.80,0:20:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If you make it hard on them,\Nthey won’t love you’
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.17,0:20:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,—Satan said that\Nabout Jehovah and individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.64,0:20:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would be giving in to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.84,0:21:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The strong feelings I had
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.08,0:21:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and my sorrow almost made me stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.55,0:21:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed a lot\Nto go back to the Kingdom Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The congregation cried;\Nthey lost a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.06,0:21:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t just Gary and Beth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.49,0:21:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They lost a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.49,0:21:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They cried,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.53,0:21:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn’t feel alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.50,0:21:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we hugged; we cried together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.71,0:21:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It really benefited us to get right back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.94,0:21:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,into spiritual focus\Nand to get our minds off ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could’ve given in\Nto my pain and thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.05,0:21:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, I’m too heartbroken.’
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.92,0:21:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me have more joy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.95,0:21:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because I realized that now they have a hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.06,0:21:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,People around us were vital
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.43,0:21:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—the support system Jehovah has—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.46,0:21:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and his Word, his spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.76,0:21:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered those prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.90,0:22:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal was really to stay
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.54,0:22:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in the full-time ministry\N(maybe doing something else),
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.11,0:22:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but we never, ever thought\Nwe would be in the circuit work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.68,0:22:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But to have our daughter\Nworking with her husband in the circuit work
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.85,0:22:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s almost hard\Nto believe that it’s happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.65,0:22:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to seeing Jerod again,\Nhaving him back with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.25,0:22:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m waiting,\Nand I know I’m not going to be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How encouraging to know that Gary and Beth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.50,0:22:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,are able to take vacation time\Nto travel occasionally
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.57,0:22:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to see their daughter and her husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.44,0:22:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who are also serving in the traveling work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.87,0:22:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you notice how Gary, Beth, and Jerod
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,felt Jehovah’s loving support as they prayed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.61,0:22:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout this heart-wrenching trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.55,0:22:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked for wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.85,0:22:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when seeking medical treatment for Jerod.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.56,0:22:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah put his arms around them and listened
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.63,0:23:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when they felt overwhelmed\Nwith grief and negative feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.10,0:23:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He strengthened\NJerod’s hope in the resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.13,0:23:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and helped Brother and Sister Septer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.70,0:23:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,stay spiritually strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.37,0:23:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Can there be any doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.88,0:23:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was answering their prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.05,0:23:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t that strengthen our conviction
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.05,0:23:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah will also answer Jerod’s prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.72,0:23:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that they all will be together again?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.06,0:23:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Jehovah didn’t miraculously cure Jerod.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.79,0:23:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But through his endurance and strong faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.26,0:23:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerod gave a witness to the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.57,0:23:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that even a child that trusts in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.87,0:23:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,can prove his loyalty to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.04,0:23:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, other situations
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.28,0:23:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,may turn out differently\Nand not end up in death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.08,0:23:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If an individual feels that relief
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.52,0:24:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was because of Jehovah’s intervention,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,he should certainly give thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.43,0:24:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we must recognize that Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.50,0:24:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the best way to handle matters
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.13,0:24:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it results in honor to his name
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.87,0:24:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the lasting good of his servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.17,0:24:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it’s worth mentioning that the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.24,0:24:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,often connects\Nour remaining spiritually alert
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.68,0:24:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with our need to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.02,0:24:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew 26:41,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.59,0:24:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.49,0:24:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep on the watch and pray continually.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Peter 4:7,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.83,0:24:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.67,0:24:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the end of all things has drawn close.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.17,0:24:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, be sound in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.91,0:24:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and be vigilant with a view to prayers.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.54,0:24:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, our prayers are so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.21,0:25:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Our personal prayers will help us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.75,0:25:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to remain spiritually alert\Nand active in God’s service
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.55,0:25:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as we await the great tribulation
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.26,0:25:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that lies just ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.29,0:25:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So in summary, our prayers to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.03,0:25:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,reveal the closeness\Nof our relationship with him
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.13,0:25:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the degree of our dependence upon him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.21,0:25:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They show the trueness of our faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.21,0:25:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the depth of our devotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.78,0:25:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the genuineness of our appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.71,0:25:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Our prayers also help us\Nto remain spiritually alert
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.29,0:25:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as we endure these last days
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.99,0:25:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,before the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.72,0:25:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll be drawn even closer to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.23,0:25:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when we learn to recognize\Nhis answers to our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.03,0:25:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we can be assured that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.57,0:25:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will not fail in giving us\Nthe desires of our heart
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.07,0:26:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as we continue rendering him sacred service.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.71,0:26:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,May we all cherish our marvelous,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.35,0:26:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous privilege of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.72,0:26:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at one practical example
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.12,0:26:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of when prayer is of utmost importance
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.63,0:26:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—when confronted\Nwith the powers of wicked spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.46,0:26:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritism is very real and dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.73,0:26:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, with Jehovah’s help,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.94,0:26:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,people can break free from its hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.17,0:26:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.41,0:26:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how one sister\Nhelped her Bible student to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.05,0:26:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma and I were so worried
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.66,0:26:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,about her Bible study, Palesa.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.09,0:26:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She had spent another sleepless night
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.33,0:26:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,after again hearing\Nher dead grandmother’s voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.30,0:27:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,plus the sound of slamming doors\Nand items crashing in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.61,0:27:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Palesa had put an amulet\Non her baby’s wrist for protection,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.52,0:27:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but the terror continued all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.66,0:27:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it wasn’t really her grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.96,0:27:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing in the house was broken;
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.70,0:27:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but the attack was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.34,0:27:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Stories about the spirit world weren’t new to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.88,0:27:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Our neighbors, the people I work with,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.31,0:27:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the people in our territory
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.35,0:27:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—almost everyone believes in spirits,\Nwhether they admit it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.89,0:27:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No—more than believe—they fear them!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.83,0:28:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I had only been studying the Bible\Nabout six months longer than Palesa.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.70,0:28:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But my study had proved to me\Nthat wicked spirits are here on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.04,0:28:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that they try to interact with people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.97,0:28:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they are dangerous enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.21,0:28:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma called the elders for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.88,0:28:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t want us to handle\Nthe situation on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.26,0:28:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As Emma told the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.53,0:28:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to speak up and tell the elders\Nthat she was leaving things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.34,0:28:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was surprised when the elders\Nsaid they didn’t need all the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.34,0:28:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They explained that while we are aware\Nof the danger the demons pose,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.35,0:28:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we do not spend time\Ntalking about their activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.28,0:28:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Jesus, when he was on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.22,0:29:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,could have told his disciples many stories
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.22,0:29:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about the doings of wicked spirits,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.96,0:29:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead,\Nhe focused on Jehovah and His activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.96,0:29:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We should do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.20,0:29:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of telling stories about what the demons
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.50,0:29:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,may or may not have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.04,0:29:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders skillfully used the Bible,\Nshepherding everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.48,0:29:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We read Ephesians 6:11:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“Put on the complete suit of armor from God
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.65,0:29:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that you may be able to stand firm
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.65,0:29:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,against the crafty acts of the Devil.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.06,0:29:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Those instructions were so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.09,0:29:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A soldier would be vulnerable\Nif he only wore part of his armor
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.10,0:29:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or if he didn’t keep it in good repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.34,0:29:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we read Ephesians 4:27:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.48,0:29:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not give the Devil an opportunity.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.52,0:30:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders explained to Palesa
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.52,0:30:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that the string around her daughter’s wrist
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.65,0:30:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is not part of the armor from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it is giving Satan\Nan opportunity to continue to harass the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.86,0:30:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers reminded us\Nthat anyone who wants Jehovah’s protection
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.47,0:30:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,must completely break free
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.60,0:30:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from anything associated with superstition,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.51,0:30:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritism, and demon worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.14,0:30:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would ever choose to side\Nwith wicked spirits instead of with Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.79,0:30:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma reminded Palesa\Nof how urgent the situation was.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.49,0:30:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But only Palesa could decide what she would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.15,0:31:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be a loyal servant of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.58,0:31:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why I’m getting baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.35,0:31:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve decided not to listen to or tell
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.56,0:31:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,any more stories about the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.19,0:31:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But more than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.19,0:31:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to look at other parts of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.53,0:31:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I doing anything\Nthat would “give the Devil an opportunity”?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.33,0:31:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly,\Nthere are still changes I need to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.57,0:31:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice how they prayed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.58,0:31:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.08,0:31:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They followed the principle of Psalm 37:5:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.32,0:31:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Commit your way to Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.62,0:31:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,rely on him, and he will act in your behalf.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.82,0:31:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you noticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.59,0:31:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as he’s committing\Nhis life course to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.83,0:31:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas’ Christian conscience\Nhas now started to guide him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.83,0:32:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And he likely realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.17,0:32:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that he has to safeguard his heart\Nfrom things that may tempt him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.17,0:32:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In this Bethel Morning Worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.98,0:32:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Morris of the Governing Body\Nhelps us to see why it requires
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.21,0:32:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,effort to protect \Nour relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.05,0:32:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I thought we’d talk about accepting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.25,0:32:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the facts about our figurative heart
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.42,0:32:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and how that safeguards
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.62,0:32:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,our relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.83,0:32:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read the day’s text
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.00,0:32:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in its entirety
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.93,0:32:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jeremiah chapter 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.33,0:32:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a sobering inspired thought
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.87,0:32:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,from our heavenly Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.71,0:32:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah chapter 17
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.24,0:32:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read verse 9:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.91,0:32:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“The heart is more treacherous
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.72,0:32:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else and is desperate.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.92,0:32:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.92,0:32:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.92,0:32:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Jehovah makes very clear to us
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.43,0:33:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—that each and every one of us\Nhas to deal with a treacherous,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.10,0:33:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or deceitful, figurative heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.40,0:33:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And how encompassing
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.40,0:33:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.70,0:33:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“more treacherous than anything else.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.57,0:33:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And what complicates it even more\Nis that it’s desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.71,0:33:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It always wants its way
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.68,0:33:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—so a lot to meditate on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.02,0:33:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And now,\NJehovah put it here for the very reason
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.75,0:33:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have to accept this fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.02,0:33:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And to safeguard our relationship with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.99,0:33:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to accept that this is the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.33,0:33:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could be a fine Christian for many years
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.67,0:33:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—mature, nice outlook, nice attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.01,0:33:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you ever find yourself\Nforgetting Jehovah’s estimation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.78,0:33:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we have within us,\Nin our figurative heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.01,0:33:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then we’re in danger\Nbecause the Devil will always exploit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.49,0:34:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that our imperfect figurative hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.52,0:34:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are treacherous and deceitful
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.92,0:34:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,more than anything else\Nand are desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.36,0:34:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So accept that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.66,0:34:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not that we want to dwell on it,\Nand you start feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.53,0:34:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, what a miserable person I am!’
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.94,0:34:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though that is something\Nthe apostle Paul acknowledged,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.57,0:34:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s just accepting the fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.57,0:34:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we’re cautious about allowing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.68,0:34:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the treacherous heart to lead us astray.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.01,0:34:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, perhaps you haven’t thought\Nabout this in a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.62,0:34:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but notice what Jesus said
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.69,0:34:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—a fundamental truth for all of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.02,0:34:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,here in Matthew chapter 6
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.79,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we sometimes\Nrefer to as the model prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew chapter 6
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.93,0:34:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,(and a lot of spiritual food for thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.94,0:34:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, anything Jesus said\Nis spiritual food for thought)
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.94,0:34:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 13 of Matthew chapter 6:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.95,0:35:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“And do not bring us into temptation,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.15,0:35:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but deliver us from the wicked one.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.09,0:35:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s been there for all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.09,0:35:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We could personally reflect on,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.10,0:35:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‘When was the last time we mentioned\Nthat in a prayer to our Father, Jehovah:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.10,0:35:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘“Do not bring us into temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.31,0:35:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but deliver us from the wicked one,”\Nor “rescue us from the wicked one”?’
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.71,0:35:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we really saying there?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.55,0:35:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re asking our heavenly Father\Nto guide and help us
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.42,0:35:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we’re not “overreached by Satan”\N—very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.42,0:35:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But the closer we get to the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.36,0:35:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,make no mistake, it’s even more urgent
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.83,0:35:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep in mind the need\Nto beg Jehovah not to bring us into temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.83,0:35:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and to guide us so that we’ll be delivered
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.40,0:36:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from this wicked one\Nwho wants to exploit the fact that we have
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.04,0:36:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a treacherous,\Ntraitorous figurative heart
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.61,0:36:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that can ruin our relationship\Nwith Jehovah personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.95,0:36:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the apostle Paul recognized this,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.39,0:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s quite interesting what he wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.46,0:36:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to his beloved brothers\Nin Thessalonians, that first letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.46,0:36:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you’d find 1 Thessalonians,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.50,0:36:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in chapter 3,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.33,0:36:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I found this quite revealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.54,0:36:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And tying in with the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.21,0:36:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of accepting the facts\Nabout how our figurative heart
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.54,0:36:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,safeguards our relationship\Nwith our God and Father, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.48,0:36:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Thessalonians 3:5,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.49,0:36:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul writes: “That is why,\Nwhen I could bear it no longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.49,0:36:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“I sent to learn of your faithfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.03,0:36:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“[now notice] in case somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.40,0:36:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Tempter might have tempted you,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.63,0:37:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and our labor\Nmight have turned out to be in vain.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.84,0:37:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn’t get into any specific detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.44,0:37:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But it helps us to appreciate\Nthat there’s this danger that somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.44,0:37:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the Tempter, Satan the Devil,\Nmight tempt us,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.02,0:37:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is connected with the need to beg
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.82,0:37:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah to deliver us, or rescue us,\Nfrom the wicked one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.79,0:37:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in his effort to tempt us to break our integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.03,0:37:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and have our cherished relationship\Nwith Jehovah be damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.03,0:37:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So he knows the heart is treacherous.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.77,0:37:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And whoever we are and however long\Nwe’ve been in the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.27,0:37:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,remember what Paul wrote to the Thessalonians
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.91,0:37:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—“somehow”—\Nbecause he’s always looking
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.38,0:37:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to somehow lead us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.91,0:37:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,into breaking our integrity to Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.55,0:37:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you think of Revelation chapter 12
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.75,0:37:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and where we are in this stream of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.39,0:38:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,(this occurred to me\Nwhen preparing these thoughts here)
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.46,0:38:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation chapter 12\Nhas very familiar thoughts here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.17,0:38:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Devil is expelled from the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.47,0:38:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he and the demons, and notice
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.37,0:38:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the familiar verse 12\Nof Revelation chapter 12:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.54,0:38:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,‘On this account be glad, you heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.88,0:38:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and [boy, they’re rejoicing]\Nthose that reside in them!’
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.45,0:38:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s an exclamation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.75,0:38:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, though:\N“Woe for the earth and for the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.29,0:38:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“because the Devil has come down to you,\Nhaving great anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.06,0:38:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that he has a short period of time.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.10,0:38:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that was true\Nafter he was ousted from the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.77,0:38:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.17,0:38:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s sobering.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.77,0:38:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to safeguard\Nour relationship with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.27,0:38:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because notice verse 17 of the same chapter:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.88,0:38:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“So the dragon became enraged.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.25,0:38:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Great anger—he’s enraged,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.82,0:39:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s waging war with the remnant,\Nas it brings out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.69,0:39:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And those that observe\Nthe commandments of God
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.86,0:39:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—anyone supporting the remnant—\Nthis is a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.36,0:39:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the war\Nis that he’s out to somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.80,0:39:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,cause us to break our integrity to our precious
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.67,0:39:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,heavenly Father,\Nso this helps us to appreciate that,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.01,0:39:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,even though it was long before
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.08,0:39:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts here in Revelation\Nand what Jesus taught us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.48,0:39:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In Proverbs chapter 4,\Nit still helps us:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.82,0:39:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“More than all else that is to be guarded,\Nsafeguard your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.45,0:39:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for out of it are the sources of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.56,0:39:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So even back then,\Nthere was the recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.26,0:39:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have to safeguard our heart\Nand accept the fact that our heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.97,0:39:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our figurative heart, is treacherous
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.44,0:39:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’ll safeguard our precious relationship\Nwith Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to help us with that,\Nnotice what Paul wrote
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.98,0:40:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—very familiar verses in 2 Timothy chapter 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.65,0:40:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve used this\Nin the ministry many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.66,0:40:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet think about it as it connects
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.72,0:40:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with safeguarding our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.96,0:40:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and accepting the fact that it’s treacherous
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.60,0:40:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we won’t break our integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.37,0:40:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or allow the Devil\Nto somehow cause us to break our integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.34,0:40:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Timothy chapter 3\Nand you’ll notice what we’re emphasizing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.34,0:40:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is in verse 16:\N“All Scripture is inspired of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.91,0:40:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice the benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.92,0:40:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s “for teaching,” it’s “for reproving,”\N“setting things straight”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.65,0:40:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—see the point here, though?—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.65,0:40:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“for disciplining in righteousness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.09,0:40:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think of that maybe on your Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.89,0:40:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I use the Bible to discipline\Nmy Bible study to get God’s thinking.’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.53,0:40:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s appropriate that elders\Nuse the Scriptures to discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.14,0:40:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we want to emphasize here for you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.87,0:41:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you’re doing your\Npersonal Bible reading (many of us),
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.25,0:41:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,let the Scriptures discipline\Nthat treacherous heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.68,0:41:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.95,0:41:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When something hits you\Nbecause maybe you’ve had wrong thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.29,0:41:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,(could be all sorts of things,\Nanything that could lead us astray
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.63,0:41:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and cause us to break our integrity),\Njust face the fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.73,0:41:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just between you and Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.73,0:41:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re reading it,\Nand let it discipline you in righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.74,0:41:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what’s going\Nto enable us to protect
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.87,0:41:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,our precious relationship\Nwith Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.74,0:41:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all have to face that fact,\Nas we mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.88,0:41:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,our figurative heart is treacherous;\Nit’s a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.35,0:41:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wonderful is we’re confident\Nthat Jehovah loves us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.49,0:41:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he made that estimation in Jeremiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.29,0:41:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s motivated by his love.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.29,0:41:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So that helps us to protect\Nour relationship with him
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.23,0:41:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—facing that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.23,0:42:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.83,0:42:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So indeed, we accept the fact\Nabout our figurative heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.97,0:42:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re determined\Nto protect and safeguard
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.78,0:42:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,our precious relationship with Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.71,0:42:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, praying for Jehovah’s help
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.32,0:42:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is an important tool\Nin safeguarding our heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.19,0:42:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And having a desire\Nto protect our relationship with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.56,0:42:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is closely linked to how much\Nwe appreciate what he’s done for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.63,0:42:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Our appreciation moves us to action
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.50,0:42:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and strengthens our faith in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.87,0:42:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Such appreciation\Nis highlighted in this month’s
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.21,0:42:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,music video which is entitled Thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.62,0:42:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dandelions growing\Non top of the hill,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.29,0:43:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mountains in the distance,\Nwind blowing through the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.27,0:43:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Warmth of the sun\Ncasting down from the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.00,0:43:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Birds fly up above,\NClouds rolling by—
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.08,0:43:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I do\NTo see such beauty?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.65,0:43:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do I do\NTo show how much I care?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.49,0:43:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be thankful,\NTell Jehovah in prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.46,0:43:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That I’m thankful\NFor the love that he shares.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.07,0:43:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, \Nlook around,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a moment,\Nand let it sink down in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.87,0:43:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Never take for granted\Nall he’s done.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.08,0:44:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be thankful.\NI’ve got to be thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.29,0:44:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So many colors\Nnow painted in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.40,0:44:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful canvas\Nyou’ve laid before my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.57,0:44:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of the river\Nrunning into the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.74,0:44:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars are dancing\Nin the moon’s spotlight—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.81,0:44:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I do\NTo see such beauty?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.09,0:44:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know what to do\NTo show how much I care.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.06,0:44:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be thankful,\NTell Jehovah in prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.76,0:44:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That I’m thankful\NFor the love that he shares.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.64,0:44:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop,\Nlook around,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.64,0:44:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a moment,\Nand let it sink down in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.18,0:45:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Never take for granted \Nall he’s done.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.08,0:45:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.09,0:45:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see your wisdom\Nand your strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.63,0:45:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your goodness in ev’rything,\NAnd how much you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.10,0:45:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m so thankful;\NI’ve got to be thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.86,0:45:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be thankful,\NTell Jehovah in prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.53,0:45:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That I’m thankful\NFor the love that he shares.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.64,0:46:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop,\Nlook around,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.04,0:46:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a moment,\Nand let it sink down in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.31,0:46:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Never take for granted\Nall he’s done.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.42,0:46:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to be thankful.\NI’ve got to be thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.33,0:46:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve got to be thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.35,0:46:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice one way\Nof expressing our gratitude to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.82,0:46:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, by means of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.65,0:46:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Having that channel\Nto the Sovereign of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.36,0:46:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is a benefit of being his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.06,0:46:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of being Jehovah’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.50,0:47:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in last month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.63,0:47:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we had an opportunity\Nto visit one of the museums
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.20,0:47:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at world headquarters in Warwick, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.37,0:47:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s more to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.54,0:47:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s join Brother John Ekrann,\Na helper to the Coordinators’ Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.45,0:47:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,on another visit, and this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.35,0:47:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll stop by a museum called\N“A People for Jehovah’s Name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.59,0:47:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you enjoy a good story?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.10,0:47:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, you’re in for a special treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.27,0:47:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“A People for Jehovah’s Name”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.47,0:47:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at world headquarters in Warwick\Nis more than a history museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.94,0:47:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the modern-day story of a people\Nseeking to know the true God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.78,0:47:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and to do his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.78,0:47:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But this isn’t just any story
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.88,0:47:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s our story.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.88,0:47:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s take\Na thrilling journey back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.66,0:47:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The story unfolds on the narrative wall
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.03,0:48:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and in several galleries along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.86,0:48:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin in the 1870’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.86,0:48:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,when a small group\Nin Allegheny, Pennsylvania,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.53,0:48:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to reexamine the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.34,0:48:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As C. T. Russell reasoned:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.14,0:48:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All the creeds of Christendom
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.31,0:48:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,claim to be founded on the Bible;
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.31,0:48:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are conflicting.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.51,0:48:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible that the Bible\Nhas been misrepresented?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.75,0:48:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The more they learned,\Nthe more they wanted to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.52,0:48:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So in 1879,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.52,0:48:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they began publishing Zion’s Watch Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.36,0:48:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Readers were soon taking a stand\Nfor the truths that they were learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.50,0:48:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.23,0:48:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What I want to tell you is this,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.20,0:48:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I am free!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.27,0:48:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth has made me free!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.24,0:48:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To-day I was excluded\Nfrom the Baptist church . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.88,0:48:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I am all alone in the ‘flesh,’\Nbut not in the ‘spirit.’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.12,0:48:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They became known as the Bible Students,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.95,0:49:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and they soon realized that people\Neverywhere should hear the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.36,0:49:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But how could this small group\Npreach the Bible’s message earthwide?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.10,0:49:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcontinental and international tours
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.90,0:49:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,helped them to see how they could expand
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.04,0:49:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,their preaching work even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.70,0:49:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In just one tour
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.71,0:49:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning in December 1911,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.21,0:49:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,C. T. Russell and his associates
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.54,0:49:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,traveled completely around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.55,0:49:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s imagine what it was like\Nto live in those exciting times.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.95,0:49:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In this gallery,\Nyou can experience what life was like
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.29,0:49:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for a pilgrim,\Nor what we today call a circuit overseer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.73,0:49:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a pilgrim’s formal jacket\Nthat he’d wear when giving a public talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.67,0:49:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible Students offered the Studies\Nin the Scriptures series in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.77,0:49:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And they carried lists to locate
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.61,0:49:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and visit Watch Tower subscribers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.11,0:49:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in 1914,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.81,0:50:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,they presented\Nthe exciting “Photo-Drama of Creation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.95,0:50:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Its purpose was to build faith in the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.32,0:50:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as God’s inspired Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.16,0:50:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an innovative combination
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.03,0:50:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of moving pictures,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.13,0:50:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,sound recordings,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.33,0:50:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and beautiful, hand-colored glass slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.00,0:50:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of people reenacted Bible scenes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.71,0:50:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,some with live animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.67,0:50:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this enormous work worth all the effort?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.51,0:50:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,DEAR BROTHER RUSSELL,\NI want to thank you;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.82,0:50:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, . . . so much, for the privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.45,0:50:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of seeing the PHOTO-DRAMA OF CREATION!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.62,0:50:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had never thought to live to see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.02,0:50:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the everlasting Gospel preached\Nto those who dwell on the earth . . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.46,0:50:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet so it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.46,0:50:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Words cannot tell you how my heart rejoices!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.03,0:50:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—Your sister, F. E. Riley.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.20,0:51:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of 1914,\Nover nine million had viewed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.01,0:51:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But with such success,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.01,0:51:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible Students didn’t realize\Nwhat tests lay ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.22,0:51:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gentile Times have ended;
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.92,0:51:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,their kings have had their day!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.33,0:51:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know not what awaits us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.87,0:51:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I broke out in 1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.37,0:51:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in 1916,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.20,0:51:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the death of C. T. Russell\Nleft the Bible Students in shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.71,0:51:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a unique time of testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.95,0:51:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside the organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.95,0:51:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,some struggled over who should take the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.62,0:51:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.62,0:51:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,governments tried to force them\Nto take sides in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.26,0:51:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in 1918,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.39,0:51:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,J. F. Rutherford\Nand seven of his close associates
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.70,0:51:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,were imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.70,0:52:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this the end for the Bible Students?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.20,0:52:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or would they prove to be
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.27,0:52:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a people for Jehovah’s name?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.21,0:52:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy that came\Nwith the release of our brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.91,0:52:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Atlanta Federal Prison on Tuesday,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.41,0:52:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,March 25, 1919, knew no bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.15,0:52:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Their further devotion to Jehovah\Nwas shown in the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.29,0:52:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that they immediately set to work to herald
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.62,0:52:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,forth to the people of God everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.46,0:52:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowledge of Jehovah’s deliverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.83,0:52:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—Thomas Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.90,0:52:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible Students\Nmoved forward with renewed zeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.10,0:52:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But the opposition didn’t end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.98,0:52:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In this gallery,\Nyou will see how our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.28,0:52:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,have stood firm for their faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.85,0:52:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In Russia, a father imprisoned for ten years
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.12,0:52:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraged his young daughters
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.12,0:52:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with hand-drawn postcards.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.92,0:52:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.13,0:53:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a son used the same blanket in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.93,0:53:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that his father used\Nwhen imprisoned before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.37,0:53:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an encouraging reminder\Nof his father’s integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.17,0:53:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.20,0:53:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnesses were locked in tiny cells
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.27,0:53:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for up to 30 days at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.78,0:53:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When you stand in the lighted outline,\Nyou get a sense of what it was like.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.38,0:53:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these brothers and sisters\Nlooked beyond the prison bars
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.79,0:53:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to their firm hope for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.73,0:53:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As light from God’s Word increased,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.86,0:53:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible Students humbly let go
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.86,0:53:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of cherished but unscriptural traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.07,0:53:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Songs used in worship were examined\Nin the light of what the Bible taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.64,0:53:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The people for Jehovah’s name\Nwere becoming even more evident.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.34,0:53:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So in 1931,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.98,0:53:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they were thrilled to take on their new name
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.65,0:53:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.35,0:54:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in 1935,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.35,0:54:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Rutherford identified\Nthe great multitude of other sheep,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.99,0:54:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who served alongside the anointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.56,0:54:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At the climax of his talk, he asked:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.26,0:54:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Will all those who have the hope\Nof living forever on the earth please stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.90,0:54:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,With this new understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.91,0:54:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they saw the true scope\Nof Jesus’ commission to make disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.51,0:54:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,New and innovative methods were needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.72,0:54:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our third gallery shows the preaching\Nmethods used in the 1930’s and 1940’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.02,0:54:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Radio was a powerful way\Nto spread the Kingdom message
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.63,0:54:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to large audiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.90,0:54:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They also used large phonographs,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.43,0:54:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,called portable transcription machines,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.27,0:54:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with loudspeakers mounted on sound cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.71,0:54:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers played recorded talks\Nwherever people gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.94,0:55:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Lighter phonographs\Nwere also designed and produced so publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.65,0:55:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,could take the recorded message\Ndirectly to people at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.55,0:55:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These methods \Nhelped bring unity to the message,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.56,0:55:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but the time had come to train each one
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.26,0:55:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s people\Nto be an effective Witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.96,0:55:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Schools were started.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.96,0:55:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Course in Theocratic Ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.60,0:55:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,trained publishers in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.34,0:55:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Bible School of Gilead
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.84,0:55:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,began training missionaries\Nfor global expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.91,0:55:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We had entered\Ninto a new era of divine education.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.02,0:55:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were about to receive an amazing tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.69,0:55:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.69,0:55:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we received the New World Translation\Nof the Christian Greek Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.29,0:55:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And by 1961, the complete Bible was released.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.93,0:55:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then,\Nwe’ve seen our tools continue to improve
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.13,0:55:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wise use of modern technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.64,0:55:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,From high-speed printing\Nto the Internet and video,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.61,0:56:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,these methods help us to stay unified,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.64,0:56:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach millions with the good news,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.64,0:56:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and to glorify God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.11,0:56:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this museum’s story is about people,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.35,0:56:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but not just any people.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.39,0:56:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We are “a people for Jehovah’s name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.82,0:56:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one question remains:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.96,0:56:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you contribute\Nto this wonderful story?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.03,0:56:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This month, after discussing the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.53,0:56:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Cherish Your Privilege of Prayer,”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.00,0:56:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw how we should act
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.00,0:56:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when we encounter spiritism.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.21,0:56:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When counteracting wicked spirits,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.31,0:56:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,praying for Jehovah’s guidance\Nis very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.91,0:56:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, Brother Morris\Nshowed us the importance of praying
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.58,0:56:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect our heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.62,0:56:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And the music video
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.62,0:56:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,reminded us\Nof not forgetting to thank Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.59,0:56:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for everything he’s given us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.13,0:56:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The provision of communicating with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.70,0:57:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is a privilege we have of being his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.57,0:57:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A visit to Warwick Bethel\Nshowed us how Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.67,0:57:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,has guided his people in modern times.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.51,0:57:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we conclude,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.54,0:57:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll visit the remote translation office
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.88,0:57:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chinle, Arizona, in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.48,0:57:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Located\Nin the southwestern part of the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.22,0:57:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the region is home
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.22,0:57:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to many native peoples and tribes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.43,0:57:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,European settlers arrived in the 1500’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.80,0:57:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the many years since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.27,0:57:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,many of the tribes were able
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.27,0:57:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to retain their culture and language.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.61,0:57:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently,\Nthe United States branch translates
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.31,0:57:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,into several indigenous languages, including
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.28,0:57:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Cherokee, Hopi, Lakota, and Navajo.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.85,0:57:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,To help with that work,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.99,0:57:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2015, a remote translation office, or RTO,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.86,0:57:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was built in Chinle,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.89,0:58:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in the heart of the Navajo nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.90,0:58:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 100 volunteers,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.90,0:58:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of which 13 are full-time servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.90,0:58:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,work at the RTO.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.91,0:58:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Navajo field has over 430 publishers,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.91,0:58:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,including approximately 130 regular pioneers
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.35,0:58:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and some 20 special pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.45,0:58:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The literature, videos,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.82,0:58:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and audio publications translated
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.29,0:58:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,at the RTO
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.29,0:58:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,are distributed to 8 Navajo congregations,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.26,0:58:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,11 groups, and 5 pregroups.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.16,0:58:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For the past five years,\Nthree-day regional conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.63,0:58:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,have been held in the Navajo language.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.04,0:58:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2018, they had a peak attendance of 471,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.04,0:58:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with one baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.05,0:58:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The volunteers at the RTO in Chinle
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.58,0:58:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,send their warm Christian love\Nto all of us around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.12,0:59:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And we love them dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.29,0:59:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.59,0:59:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from the World Headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
